{
    "name":  "Turkey Wild Rice Soup",
    "instructions":  "1. Melt the butter in a soup pot over medium heat. Add the onion and celery; cook and stir until translucent, about 5 minutes.  \n\n2. Stir in the flour, and cook until it turns a pale, yellowish-brown color, 3 to 5 minutes.  \n\n3. Gradually whisk in the turkey broth until smooth and no lumps of flour remain.  \n\n4. Stir in the carrots and bring mixture to a simmer. Cook, whisking constantly, until stock is thick and smooth and carrots are tender, about 2 minutes.  \n\n5. Stir in the turkey, wild rice, almonds, salt, and pepper; simmer until heated through, about 5 minutes.  \n\n6. Stir in the lemon juice and half-and-half; heat until just below a boil. Serve immediately.",
    "simpleInstructions":  "1. Cook onion and celery in butter.  \n\n2. Add flour and cook until brown.  \n\n3. Whisk in broth.  \n\n4. Add carrots and simmer.  \n\n5. Add turkey, rice, almonds, salt, and pepper; simmer.  \n\n6. Stir in lemon juice and half-and-half; heat.",
